# These directories live IN the chezmoi source tree but are NOT meant to be
# deployed to ~/. They are consumed in-place by the deploy script:
#   - system_nixos/   → copied to /etc/nixos/ by `bash system_scripts/deploy-nixos.sh`
#   - system_scripts/ → invoked directly from the source dir (deploy-nixos.sh, notify/, monitor/, etc.)
#   - docs/           → reference docs read in source
# Without this ignore, chezmoi creates duplicate copies at ~/system_nixos/
# and ~/system_scripts/ that nothing reads, and the deploy script's
# `nix flake update` step makes them appear as drift on every subsequent
# pre-flight check (`chezmoi status` reports them as Modified).
system_nixos
system_scripts
docs
